In 1974, at the age of 18, Schulz joined the SPD, became involved with the Young Socialists and in 1984 was elected to the WÃ¼rselen Municipal Council, remaining a member for just over two electoral terms, to 1998, from 1987 onwards as mayor. At 31, he was then the youngest mayor in North Rhine-Westphalia. He held that office until 1998.